data.enText: to think or accept that sth is true but without having proof of it

data.chText: 认为经济将继续好转是有道理的。
data.enText: It is reasonable to assume (that) the economy will continue to improve.

data.chText: 咱们暂时假设计划成功。
data.enText: Let us assume for a moment that the plan succeeds.

data.chText: 他认为，她会在通常时间回到家的。
data.enText: She would, he assumed, be home at the usual time.

data.chText: 普遍认为，紧张是工作过重所致。
data.enText: It is generally assumed that stress is caused by too much work.
Don't always assume the worst (= that sth bad has happened) .

data.chText: 在这个例子中我们已假定单价为10元。
data.enText: In this example we have assumed a unit price of $10.

data.chText: 我本以为他是比利时人。

data.hoverText: 动词+名词短语+带to的不定式

data.enText: I had assumed him to be a Belgian.

data.chText: 承担（责任）；就（职）；取得（权力）
data.enText: to take or begin to have power or responsibility

data.chText: 法庭承担了保障这个女孩福利的责任。
data.enText: The court assumed responsibility for the girl's welfare.

data.chText: 反叛武装力量已控制了首都。
data.enText: Rebel forces have assumed control of the capital.

data.chText: 呈现（外观、样子）；显露（特征）
data.enText: to begin to have a particular quality or appearance
This matter has assumed considerable importance.

data.chText: 在这个故事中神以鹰的形象出现。
data.enText: In the story the god assumes the form of an eagle.
to pretend to have a particular feeling or quality
He assumed an air of concern.

simple_means.memory_skill: as 加强 + sum 拿，取 + e → 拿住 → 承担〔责任〕

ex.chText: 我没看见你的手机，所以我以为你离开了。
ex.enText: I didn't see your cell phone, so I assumed you'd left.

ex.chText: 假设爸爸同意，你打算什么时候买新汽车？
ex.enText: Assuming that Dad agrees, when do you want to shop for a new car?

synonyms.bx: 指想当然地将未经证实的事当真，比较武断。

ex.chText: 该逻辑分析假定主体与客体是分开的。
ex.enText: This logical analysis presumes the separation of subject from object.

ex.chText: 我猜测，这个价钱包括一切交通费用和住宿费。
ex.enText: I presume that this price includes all transportation and accomodation fees.

synonyms.bx: 常指以已有的经验、信息等为依据进行合乎逻辑的推测、推断，但结论可能有误。

ex.chText: 公司的这个计划假定小麦产量会稳定增加。
ex.enText: The company's plan supposes a steady increase in wheat yield.

ex.chText: 他凭什么认为他们要离职？
ex.enText: What makes him suppose they're going to quit?

synonyms.bx: 指在某一前提条件下或根据已有知识、信息等进行推测，有时用于表达意见。

example: What should I wear today?
He put on his best suit for the wedding
The princess donned a long blue dress
The queen assumed the stately robes
He got into his jeans

tr: take on a certain form, attribute, or aspect
example: His voice took on a sad tone
The story took a new turn
he adopted an air of superiority
She assumed strange manners
The gods assume human or animal form in these fables

tr: take to be the case or to be true
example: I assume his train was late

tr: take up someone's soul into heaven
example: This is the day when May was assumed into heaven
She assumed indifference, even though she was seething with anger
he feigned sleep
He assumes the lotus position
She took her seat on the stage
We took our seats in the orchestra
She took up her position behind the tree
strike a pose

tr: seize and take control without authority and possibly with force
take as one's right or possession
example: He assumed to himself the right to fill all positions in the town
he usurped my rights
She seized control of the throne after her husband died

tr: take on as one's own the expenses or debts of another person
example: I'll accept the charges
She agreed to bear the responsibility

tr: take on titles, offices, duties, responsibilities
example: When will the new President assume office?

value.def: If you assume that something is true, you imagine that it is true, sometimes wrongly.

example.ex: It is a misconception to assume that the two continents are similar...
example.tran: 关于这两块大陆相似的假设是一种误解。

example.ex: If the package is wrapped well, we assume the contents are also wonderful...
example.tran: 如果包装精美，我们就会认为里面装的也是好东西。

example.ex: If mistakes occurred, they were assumed to be the fault of the commander on the spot...
example.tran: 如果出现了错误，就会认为是现场指挥官的失误。

value.def: If someone assumes power or responsibility, they take power or responsibility.

example.ex: Mr Cross will assume the role of Chief Executive with a team of four directors...
example.tran: 克劳斯先生将出任首席执行官，手下有4位经理。

example.ex: If there is no president, power will be assumed by the most extremist forces.
example.tran: 如果没有主席，权力就会落入最极端的过激分子手中。

value.tran: 掌管，夺取，取得（权力）；承担（责任）

value.def: If something assumes a particular quality, it begins to have that quality.

example.ex: In his dreams, the mountains assumed enormous importance.
example.tran: 在他的梦中，山有着至关重要的作用。

value.tran: 呈现，具有，显露（某种特质）

value.def: If you assume a particular expression or way of behaving, you start to look or behave in this way.

example.ex: He contented himself by assuming an air of superiority...
example.tran: 他表现出一副高高在上的样子以获得自我满足。

example.ex: Prue assumed a placatory tone of voice.
example.tran: 普吕以一种安慰人的语气说话。

value.tran: 表现出（某种表情）；装出，做出（某种样子）

value.def: You can use let us assume or let's assume when you are considering a possible situation or event, so that you can think about the consequences.

example.ex: Let us assume those clubs actually win something. Then players will receive large bonuses...
example.tran: 倘若那些俱乐部真的赚了，那么球员就会获得一大笔奖金。

example.ex: Let's assume for a moment that I am a litigant in your court.
example.tran: 暂且假设我是你的诉讼当事人。

trans: 承担责任；承担责任（或职责）

as 表加强 + sumpt 拿，取 + ion，assume 的名词 → 假设；承担

con 加强 + sum 拿，取 + ing 正…的，consume的形容词 → 消耗性的
